P(A\cap B)
\geq
1 - P(A') - P(B')
A'
S=(A\cap B) \cup A^C \cup B^C\\ \iff P(S)=P(A\cap B) + P(A^C) + P(B^C) - P(A^C \cap B^C)\\ \iff P(A\cap B) = \underbrace{P(S)}_{=1} - P(A^C) - P(B^C) + P(A^C \cap B^C).\\ \text{Now since } P(A^C \cap B^C) \geq 0,\\ P(A\cap B) \geq 1 - P(A^C) - P(B^C).
P(A\cap B) \geq 1 - P(A') - P(B') \iff P(A\cap B) + P(A') + P(B') \geq 1
(A\cap B) \cup A' \cup B'\;?
A' \cup B' = (A \cap B)'
(A\cap B) \cup (A' \cup B') = (A\cap B) \cup (A \cap B)'
x \in (A\cap B)
x \in (A\cap B)'
x \in (A\cap B)\;\;\text{OR}\;\;x \notin (A\cap B)
